HEADWORD: Elusion
<hw>E*lu"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>elusio</ets>, fr. L. <ets>eludere</ets>, elusum. See
<er>Elude</er>.]</ety> <def>Act of eluding; adroit escape, as by
artifice; a mockery; a cheat; trickery.</def>⟦br⟧
